The paper deals with query complexity, which is a topic in computational complexity theory. Specifically, it introduces new functions that demonstrate separations between various query complexity measures. This makes it likely to belong to cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also involves information theory, as it discusses the randomized and quantum query complexities of the introduced functions, making cs.IT (Information Theory) a likely category as well. Additionally, the paper introduces a new technique called pointer functions, which may make it relevant to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.QI (Quantum Physics).
